==English==
===Etymology===
[[bombardier]] + [[beetle]]

===Noun===
'''bombardier beetle''' (''plural'' '''bombardier beetles''')

# A beetle whose defence mechanism enables it to eject a hot aqueous mixture of chemicals at predators. They come from a number of subfamilies: Carabinae (eg Brachinus crepitans), Metriinae (eg Stenaptinus insignis) and Paussinae (eg Goniotropis nicaraguensis).